# Shell scripts get baked verbatim into container images (Dockerfile COPY,
# executed via their #!/bin/bash shebang) — always check them out with LF,
# regardless of a Windows clone's core.autocrlf setting. CRLF here turns the
# shebang into `#!/bin/bash\r`, which the kernel can't find and reports as
# "exec /startup.sh: no such file or directory".
*.sh text eol=lf
